All Known Implementing Classes:

public interface GaugeSetAttributes
extends GaugeAttributes

This interface contains all of the property keys and constant values needed to customize a gauge set.

LEGEND_TEXT_NUMBER_TYPE

static final java.lang.String LEGEND_TEXT_NUMBER_TYPE
See Also:
Constant Field Values
For internal use only. Application developers should not use this
Represents the number type of the legend text. This property controls how threshold numbers listed in the legend are formatted. The default will be to treat numbers as percentages (i.e. NT_PERCENT). Key : LEGEND_TEXT_NUMBER_TYPE Value : Integer, the valid constants are NT_NUMBER and NT_PERCENT. Ex: To create a value, do the following new Interger( NT_PERCENT);
